{% set defaultHrCode %}<p>The story begins...</p>
<hr />
<p>Three days later...</p>{% endset %}

{% set decorativeHrCode %}<p>The end of the scene.</p>
<hr class="decorative" />
<p>A new setting emerges.</p>{% endset %}

{% set ornamentHrCode %}<hr data-ornament="❧" />

<hr data-ornament="~ ~ ~" />

<hr data-ornament="§" />

<hr data-ornament="✦ ✦ ✦" />

<hr data-ornament="⁂" />{% endset %}

{% set blogBreakCode %}<h2>My Trip to Japan</h2>
<p>We started in Tokyo...</p>
<hr />
<p>A week later, we found ourselves in Kyoto...</p>{% endset %}

{% set footnoteBreakCode %}<p>The findings suggest a correlation<sup>1</sup>.</p>
<hr />
<p><small><sup>1</sup> Smith et al., 2023.</small></p>{% endset %}

{% set sceneBreakCode %}<p>She closed the door, knowing she would never return.</p>
<hr class="decorative" />
<p>Twenty years later, she stood at that same door.</p>{% endset %}

{% set sectionAlternativeCode %}<section>
  <h2>First Topic</h2>
  <p>Content about the first topic.</p>
</section>
<section>
  <h2>Second Topic</h2>
  <p>Content about the second topic.</p>
</section>{% endset %}

{% set cssPropertiesCode %}hr {
  border: none;
  border-block-start: var(--border-width-thin) solid var(--color-border);
  margin-block: var(--size-xl);
}

/* Decorative variant */
hr.decorative {
  border: none;
  text-align: center;

  &::before {
    content: "* * *";
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.5em;
  }
}

/* Custom ornament variant */
hr[data-ornament] {
  border: none;
  text-align: center;

  &::before {
    content: attr(data-ornament);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.25em;
  }
}{% endset %}

{% set customizationCode %}/* Thicker divider */
hr.thick {
  border-block-start-width: var(--border-width-thick);
}

/* Colored divider */
hr.accent {
  border-color: var(--color-interactive);
}

/* Tighter spacing */
hr.compact {
  margin-block: var(--size-m);
}{% endset %}

{% set ariaHiddenCode %}<hr aria-hidden="true" />{% endset %}

<!-- Overview Section -->
  <section>
    <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;hr&gt;</code> element creates a thematic break in HTML content. Despite its name, it represents a semantic break rather than just a visual line. Use it to separate sections of content that have different topics or themes.</p>

    <div class="example">
      <p>Content in the first thematic section. This paragraph discusses one topic.</p>
      <hr />
      <p>Content in the second thematic section. This paragraph shifts to a different topic.</p>
    </div>

    <code-block language="html" label="Basic horizontal rule">{{ defaultHrCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <!-- When to Use Section -->
  <section>
    <h2 id="when-to-use">When to Use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Scene changes</strong> - In stories or narratives when the setting or time changes</li>
      <li><strong>Topic shifts</strong> - When transitioning to a different subject within the same document</li>
      <li><strong>Section breaks</strong> - To separate major content areas without using a new heading</li>
      <li><strong>Before footnotes</strong> - To separate main content from endnotes or footnotes</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>When Not to Use</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Visual spacing</strong> - Use CSS margins or padding instead</li>
      <li><strong>Decorative lines</strong> - Use CSS borders on containers instead</li>
      <li><strong>Between every section</strong> - Headings already provide visual separation</li>
      <li><strong>Before/after headers or footers</strong> - Use semantic elements instead</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Default Style Section -->
  <section>
    <h2 id="default">Default Style</h2>
    <p>The default horizontal rule displays as a thin border line with vertical margin.</p>

    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/hr-default.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/hr/default" title="Default horizontal rule" shadow></browser-window>
  </section>

  <!-- Decorative Variant Section -->
  <section>
    <h2 id="decorative">Decorative Variant</h2>
    <p>The <code>.decorative</code> class creates a centered dot pattern instead of a line, useful for creative writing or less formal contexts.</p>

    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/hr-decorative.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/hr/decorative" title="Decorative horizontal rule" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Decorative horizontal rule">{{ decorativeHrCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>Use Cases for Decorative</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Scene breaks in fiction</li>
      <li>Time jumps in narratives</li>
      <li>Thought transitions in essays</li>
      <li>Section breaks in newsletters</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Custom Ornament Variant Section -->
  <section>
    <h2 id="ornament">Custom Ornament</h2>
    <p>The <code>data-ornament</code> attribute lets you specify any text or symbol as the divider content. This is more flexible than the <code>.decorative</code> class, which always uses dots.</p>

    <p>Unlike plain <code>&lt;hr&gt;</code> and <code>.decorative</code> rules, an explicit <code>data-ornament</code> value is preserved across all themes — your chosen symbol always renders as specified.</p>

    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/hr-ornaments.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/hr/ornaments" title="Custom ornament horizontal rules" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Custom ornament examples">{{ ornamentHrCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>Common Ornament Characters</h3>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Character</th>
          <th>Usage</th>
          <th>Example</th>
